'''Cardiophysics''' is an [[interdisciplinary]] [[science]] that stands at the junction of [[cardiology]] and [[medical physics]], with researchers using the methods of, and theories from, [[physics]] to study [[Cardiovascular|cardiovascular system]] at different levels of its organisation, from the molecular scale to whole organisms. Being formed historically as part of [[systems biology]], ''cardiophysics'' designed to reveal connections between the physical mechanisms, underlying the organization of the cardiovascular system, and biological features of its functioning.
Zbigniew R. Struzik seems to be a first author who used the term in a scientific publication in 2004.
One can use interchangeably also the terms ''cardiovascular physics''. <!-- == History of investigations == === Early works ===
-->
